title: Aviansie

properties.name: description
properties.value: Aviansies (sometimes referred to as aviantese[1] in plural form) are avian monsters found in the southern section of the main chamber of the God Wars Dungeon. Like other creatures within the dungeon, they can be found fighting for their god Armadyl, engaging in combat against the followers of Zamorak.

Aviansies (sometimes referred to as aviantese[1] in plural form) are avian monsters found in the southern section of the main chamber of the God Wars Dungeon. Like other creatures within the dungeon, they can be found fighting for their god Armadyl, engaging in combat against the followers of Zamorak.

The ability to be assigned aviansies can be purchased for 80 slayer reward points with the Watch the birdie slayer reward. Once unlocked, they can be toggled off. Though, in order to toggle them back on, they must be purchased again for 80 slayer points or removed from the assignments list through the use of the cancellation slots.

Unlike most other followers, however, aviansies have an increased sense of danger. Even if they are in combat with another monster, if the player attempts to attack them, the aviansie will start attacking the player immediately; this trait is shared by all Armadylean monsters.

As they are airborne, they are completely immune to melee attacks except for salamanders, and can only be damaged with either Ranged or Magic. If the player attempts to attack an aviansie with a melee weapon, the message The Aviansie is flying too high for you to attack using melee. will appear in their chatbox, and the aviansie will become aggressive and start attacking the player if it hasn't already.

Adamant bar drops from aviansies in the God Wars Dungeon will be noted for players that have completed the Hard Fremennik Diary. They also do not drop looting bags, unlike all other monsters in the Wilderness.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Avian means "of or relating to birds".
  • Aviansie come in both genders; female aviansies wear helmets and have a lower-cut platebody, while the males don't wear helmets.
    • Stat-wise, lower-leveled female aviansies have a lower Defence level than their male counterparts, but the moderate and high-level ones possess a greater Defence and Ranged level than their corresponding variant.

[[File:Aviansie icon.png|left]]
'''Aviansies''' (sometimes referred to as '''aviantese'''{{CiteNPC|npc=Knight's notes|quote=The aviantese are alive, and I suspect they still guard the Godsword!}} in plural form) are avian monsters found in the southern section of the main chamber of the [[God Wars Dungeon]]. Like other creatures within the dungeon, they can be found fighting for their god [[Armadyl]], engaging in combat against the followers of [[Zamorak]].

The ability to be assigned aviansies can be purchased for 80 [[slayer reward point]]s with the Watch the birdie slayer reward. Once unlocked, they can be toggled off. Though, in order to toggle them back on, they must be purchased again for 80 slayer points or removed from the assignments list through the use of the cancellation slots.

Unlike most other followers, however, aviansies have an increased sense of danger. Even if they are in combat with another monster, if the player attempts to attack them, the aviansie will start attacking the player immediately; this trait is shared by all Armadylean monsters.

As they are airborne, they are completely immune to [[melee]] attacks except for [[salamander]]s, and can only be damaged with either [[Ranged]] or [[Magic]]. If the player attempts to attack an aviansie with a [[melee weapon]], the message ''The Aviansie is flying too high for you to attack using melee.'' will appear in their chatbox, and the aviansie will become [[aggressive]] and start attacking the player if it hasn't already.

[[Adamant bar]] drops from aviansies in the God Wars Dungeon will be noted for players that have completed the [[Fremennik Diary#Hard|Hard Fremennik Diary]]. They also do not drop [[looting bag]]s, unlike all other monsters in the [[Wilderness]].

==Trivia==
* Avian means "of or relating to birds".
* Aviansie come in both genders; female aviansies wear helmets and have a lower-cut platebody, while the males don't wear helmets.
** Stat-wise, lower-leveled female aviansies have a lower Defence level than their male counterparts, but the moderate and high-level ones possess a greater Defence and Ranged level than their corresponding variant.
